OL,3,CBusinesses say Stroud's Night Angels
OL,4,Care 'invaluable'
OL,6,FThe team has received training from
OL,7,Fthe police and has access to radios so
OL,8,Fthey can make contact with the force
OL,9,Fcontrol room when incidents occur.
OL,11,F"On my first shift, there was quite a
OL,12,Fviolent assault. The police had to be
OL,13,Fcalled, and we had to assist to make
OL,14,Fsure it didn't go too out of hand,"
OL,15,Fsaid Rachael Summers, one of the
OL,16,Fvolunteer Night Angels.
OL,18,F"But then, you also get shifts where
OL,19,Fit's quite peaceful ` but it can
OL,20,Fchange minute to minute, hour to hour."
